    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-04T02:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-04T02:34:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">temporarily at Harbin, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-04T16:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 12, 5:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>217. I understand that the Omsk Government desires 150,000 rifles ordered in
                    America should be sent to Russians for new recruits. I understand <persName
                        corresp="#p_GMGWS1">General Graves</persName> is favorably considering this
                    matter, and I recommend that it be done. Believe it would be good policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
